{"url": "https://towardsdatascience.com/living-and-computing-on-the-edge-a-brief-introduction-to-federated-learning-a3c07bda21c0", "time": 1683003248.613811, "path": "towardsdatascience.com/living-and-computing-on-the-edge-a-brief-introduction-to-federated-learning-a3c07bda21c0/", "webpage": {"metadata": {"title": "Living and Computing on the edge. A Brief Introduction to Federated\u2026 | by Gurkamal Deol | Towards Data Science", "h1": "Living and Computing on the edge", "description": "The need for privacy has never been more immediate than now \u2014 a time where the value of data is likened to oil and considered to be an individual\u2019s most important asset. The types of data that\u2026"}, "outgoing_paragraph_urls": [{"url": "http://www.linkedin.com/in/gurkamal-deol-508675174", "anchor_text": "www.linkedin.com/in/gurkamal-deol-508675174", "paragraph_index": 11}], "all_paragraphs": ["The need for privacy has never been more immediate than now \u2014 a time where the value of data is likened to oil and considered to be an individual\u2019s most important asset. The types of data that individuals generate range from seemingly harmless details such as retail preferences to highly sensitive information like medical records, and even political views which can and have affected a national election [1].", "One possible answer \u2014 that is getting more and more traction \u2014 to this call for increased data security is the development of privacy-preserving machine learning \u2014 also known as Federated Learning. At a high level, Federated Learning is a machine learning approach that trains models collaboratively and aims to prevent data leakage by using differential privacy and decentralized data. Federated Learning thus allows an individual\u2019s data to remain anonymous while helping build powerful models [2].", "In the simplest terms, instead of sending your data to a third-party, Federated Learning brings the model to your data, while encrypting every step.", "Privacy is not the only issue that Federated Learning is being used to solve; it is also taking down barriers that currently prevent us from building models with greater accuracy. One such issue is that there is no central source to pull all the data needed to train these models. A range of data types \u2014 which are often spread across institutions \u2014 would be required to train a model that paints the whole picture. For example, to capture an individual\u2019s financial situation and provide insight, a model must be trained on data found across multiple banks and credit services, online retail behaviour, and payment habits. To add to the complexity, data transfer between departments of the same company might face administrative or privacy related issues.", "Federated Learning brings forward the opportunity for various parties who each hold a different piece of the puzzle to collaboratively train models that are more accurate than ones trained on single sources of data.", "Federated learning at a high level can be described in three steps:", "These steps ensure that the bias of each data source is taken into account and accurately illustrate the landscape of the problem. For example, training a Federated model on heart disease data from health institutions around the world could eliminate the racial and gender bias found in models trained on a nation\u2019s domestic data [3].", "I created a diagram to illustrate the various elements that comprise federated learning at a very high level:", "There are three points which form the fundamentals of federated learning: privacy, data structure, and model type. These points further branch out with new research constantly changing the landscape, increasing the complexity, and adding depth.", "While federated learning may become a solution to problems involving vast amounts of data across multiple devices \u2014 some hurdles still exist.", "Your home for data science. A Medium publication sharing concepts, ideas and codes.", "I\u2019m a ML engineer and biologist. I\u2019m Interested in AI driven drug discovery, computer vision, & federated learning. www.linkedin.com/in/gurkamal-deol-508675174"], "all_outgoing_urls": [{"url": "https://rsci.app.link/?%24canonical_url=https%3A%2F%2Fmedium.com%2Fp%2Fa3c07bda21c0&%7Efeature=LoOpenInAppButton&%7Echannel=ShowPostUnderCollection&source=---two_column_layout_nav----------------------------------", "anchor_text": "Open in app"}, {"url": "https://medium.com/m/signin?operation=register&redirect=https%3A%2F%2Ftowardsdatascience.com%2Fliving-and-computing-on-the-edge-a-brief-introduction-to-federated-learning-a3c07bda21c0&source=post_page---two_column_layout_nav-----------------------global_nav-----------", "anchor_text": "Sign up"}, {"url": "https://medium.com/m/signin?operation=login&redirect=https%3A%2F%2Ftowardsdatascience.com%2Fliving-and-computing-on-the-edge-a-brief-introduction-to-federated-learning-a3c07bda21c0&source=post_page---two_column_layout_nav-----------------------global_nav-----------", "anchor_text": "Sign In"}, {"url": "https://medium.com/?source=---two_column_layout_nav----------------------------------", "anchor_text": ""}, {"url": "https://medium.com/m/signin?operation=register&redirect=https%3A%2F%2Fmedium.com%2Fnew-story&source=---two_column_layout_nav-----------------------new_post_sidenav-----------", "anchor_text": "Write"}, {"url": "https://medium.com/search?source=---two_column_layout_nav----------------------------------", "anchor_text": ""}, {"url": "https://medium.com/m/signin?operation=register&redirect=https%3A%2F%2Ftowardsdatascience.com%2Fliving-and-computing-on-the-edge-a-brief-introduction-to-federated-learning-a3c07bda21c0&source=post_page---two_column_layout_nav-----------------------global_nav-----------", "anchor_text": "Sign up"}, {"url": "https://medium.com/m/signin?operation=login&redirect=https%3A%2F%2Ftowardsdatascience.com%2Fliving-and-computing-on-the-edge-a-brief-introduction-to-federated-learni